	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Agreed.  So I'm thinking that the CIRAM /CE pin must actually be an "output-enable".  Otherwise you would get bus contention on every read from the name/attr region of memory.  This is what was confusing me.  I should open up my NES and see if I can find the datasheet for the CIRAM SRAM chip and look at how the chip works with regards to driving its data bus.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
